headline: Gold Slips Following Fed Decision
summary: Gold futures treaded water for most of the day, and SPDR Gold shares dropped 1.1% following the quarter-point interest rate cut by the Fed.

headline: Birkenstock Aims for Firmer Footing After Tough Year for Profitability
summary: The sandal-maker is targeting healthier margins after its profitability stumbled during fiscal 2024 amid an unfavorable sales mix and investment in factory capacity.

headline: FactSet Appoints Barak Eilam to Board of Directors
summary: NORWALK, Conn., Dec. 18, 2024 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- FactSet (NYSE: FDS | NASDAQ: FDS), a global financial digital platform and enterprise solutions provider, today announced the appointment of Barak Eilam to its Board of Directors. He will also serve on FactSet’s Compensation and Talent Committee. Eilam brings nearly three decades of experience scaling enterprise software companies into global market leaders. headline: Japan Exports Continue to Recover Amid Yen Weakness
summary: Japan’s exports continued to recover in November thanks to demand for chip-making machines and nonferrous metals, official data showed.
